    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>That should be:</p>\n\n<pre><code>java -Dtest=\"true\" -jar myApplication.jar\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Then the following will return the value:</p>\n\n<pre><code>System.getProperty(\"test\");\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The value could be <code>null</code>, though, so guard against an exception using a <code>Boolean</code>:</p>\n\n<pre><code>boolean b = Boolean.parseBoolean( System.getProperty( \"test\" ) );\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Note that the <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/Boolean.html#getBoolean%28java.lang.String%29\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>getBoolean</code></a> method delegates the system property value, simplifying the code to:</p>\n\n<pre><code>if( Boolean.getBoolean( \"test\" ) ) {\n   // ...\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
