    "body" : "<p>You're giving parameters to your program instead to Java. Use</p>\n\n<pre><code>java -Dtest=\"true\" -jar myApplication.jar \n</code></pre>\n\n<p>instead.</p>\n\n<p>Consider using</p>\n\n<pre><code>\"true\".equalsIgnoreCase(System.getProperty(\"test\"))\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>to avoid the NPE. But do not use \"<em>Yoda conditions</em>\" always without thinking, sometimes throwing the NPE is the right behavior and sometimes something like</p>\n\n<pre><code>System.getProperty(\"test\") == null || System.getProperty(\"test\").equalsIgnoreCase(\"true\")\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>is right (providing default true). A shorter possibility is</p>\n\n<pre><code>!\"false\".equalsIgnoreCase(System.getProperty(\"test\"))\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>but not using double negation doesn't make it less hard to misunderstand.</p>\n"
  } ],
